    <h1>A Treatise of Human Nature</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">David Hume · 1739 · <a href="https://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/4705">Project Gutenberg</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">No amount of observed instances can logically guarantee a universal claim. Every inductive inference rests on a habit of the mind, not a chain of reasoning. Causation is something we feel, not something we prove.</p>
    </div>

